 Patterson has been following high frequency trading closely for years. 

00:22:00.400 --> 00:22:04.360
 Without knowing each other, Bodek and Patterson both ... 

00:22:04.480 --> 00:22:07.680
 analyzed conflicts of interest between the THF industry ... 

00:22:07.800 --> 00:22:10.960
 and the stock exchanges for a certain period. 

00:22:13.920 --> 00:22:17.240
 We ended up in a Starbucks in Manhattan. 

00:22:17.360 --> 00:22:23.760
 And I remember precisely, towards the end of our conversation ... 

00:22:23.880 --> 00:22:27.320
 Haim said something about ... 

00:22:27.440 --> 00:22:31.280
 illegal action in the market. 

00:22:31.400 --> 00:22:36.160
 He thought that was partly why Trading Machines had closed. 

00:22:36.320 --> 00:22:42.360
 I had an organization chart with all the people ... 

00:22:42.480 --> 00:22:45.360
 the highest placed in THF, in my bag ... 

00:22:45.480 --> 00:22:52.080
 and other data that was part of my business information. 

00:22:53.520 --> 00:22:58.120
 He had worked on it a lot, but it was very vague. 

00:22:58.240 --> 00:23:00.120
 Did you give him these documents? 

00:23:00.240 --> 00:23:02.440
 I let him take a look at it. 

00:23:02.560 --> 00:23:06.240
 I said, "You have to tell me what it is." 

00:23:06.360 --> 00:23:12.240
 I have spoken so many times in my career to people who say they know something ... 

00:23:12.360 --> 00:23:17.920
 which may be illegal, something rigged at some point. 

00:23:18.040 --> 00:23:24.440
 But they don't say more, it's still very vague. 

00:23:29.800 --> 00:23:34.680
 I remember the first interview I had with him ... 

00:23:34.800 --> 00:23:39.160
 we sat down, it must have been 10:30 am. 

00:23:39.280 --> 00:23:44.400
 And we started talking for 7 hours straight. 

00:23:44.520 --> 00:23:48.560
 I didn't eat anything, I had to drink a glass of water. 

00:23:48.680 --> 00:23:54.040
 I sat there, listened to Haim, and took notes. 

00:23:54.160 --> 00:24:00.040
 My computer's battery has run down, I took notes by hand. 

00:24:00.160 --> 00:24:02.600
 Because he really said it all. 

00:24:02.720 --> 00:24:06.840
 I'll try to explain this to you with a metaphor. 

00:24:06.960 --> 00:24:12.560
 It's a circus. I will tell you the facts through comedy. 

00:24:12.680 --> 00:24:15.880
 But unfortunately, it looks like that. 

00:24:16.000 --> 00:24:20.600
 Here's a concert hall, let's say it's Metallica playing. 

00:24:20.720 --> 00:24:26.960
 I like metal, so it's Metallica who plays in this concert hall. 

00:24:27.080 --> 00:24:29.840
 The ticket office opens at 6 p.m. 

00:24:29.960 --> 00:24:33.120
 So I'm going to stand in line. 

00:24:33.240 --> 00:24:39.960
 After a while, people arrive, I am no longer the last in line. 

00:24:40.080 --> 00:24:43.040
 There are resellers. 

00:24:44.000 --> 00:24:47.200
 They are also in the queue, with me. 

00:24:47.320 --> 00:24:52.400
 I recognize them by their t-shirt, they all wear the same. 

00:24:52.520 --> 00:24:59.280
 They are also in close collaboration with the Bourse, the concert hall. 

00:24:59.400 --> 00:25:02.080
 What kind of collaboration? 

00:25:04.600 --> 00:25:11.120
 Perhaps one of them brings a significant volume. 

00:25:11.240 --> 00:25:14.360
 That is to say, he buys a lot of tickets. 

00:25:14.480 --> 00:25:18.600
 Obviously, he sells them to the spectators. One has a lot ... 

00:25:18.720 --> 00:25:23.240
 another reseller owns 10% of the room. 

00:25:25.640 --> 00:25:29.840
 A third dealer does not have much ... 

00:25:29.960 --> 00:25:34.040
 but it largely has another room ... 

00:25:34.160 --> 00:25:39.600
 and he has a seat on the board of directors of this room. 

00:25:39.720 --> 00:25:43.360
 So there is a very close collaboration ... 

00:25:43.480 --> 00:25:47.280
 between these dealers and the concert hall. 

00:25:48.240 --> 00:25:50.760
 Metallica tickets sold on the black. 

00:25:50.880 --> 00:25:55.720
 I will draw a parallel between the opening of the counter ... 

00:25:55.840 --> 00:26:02.560
 and when a price may change, on the financial market. 

00:26:02.680 --> 00:26:07.160
 At 6 p.m. that's what I'm going to attend. 

00:26:07.280 --> 00:26:10.880
 Absolutely all these resellers ... 

00:26:11.000 --> 00:26:17.440
 will literally teleport, in a picosecond. 

00:26:17.560 --> 00:26:22.000
 They are all there in front of me. 

00:26:22.120 --> 00:26:25.680
 How come ? I ask someone who answers me: 

00:26:25.800 --> 00:26:27.720
 "They are very fast." 

00:26:27.840 --> 00:26:32.120
 I said, "No, they teleported. They were behind me." 

00:26:32.240 --> 00:26:37.720
 There is no difference between an order type and the one wearing the t-shirt. 

00:26:37.840 --> 00:26:44.200
 You add a code to your order saying, "Respect me, please." 

00:26:50.080 --> 00:26:52.240
 How did you hear about Haim Bodek? 

00:26:52.360 --> 00:26:57.480
 I met him at Blair Hull's, he invited me to dinner. 

00:26:57.600 --> 00:26:59.240
 What did you think of him? 

00:26:59.360 --> 00:27:05.040
 He's great, he knows everything, we started talking about work in 5 minutes. 

00:27:05.160 --> 00:27:11.600
 Have you noticed the same thing as him in your data? 

00:27:11.720 --> 00:27:19.640
 No, we don't know who executed an order unless ... 

00:27:19.760 --> 00:27:21.960
 We do not know who is carrying out the orders. 

00:27:22.080 --> 00:27:25.840
 But he knows who executed his. 

00:27:27.120 --> 00:27:29.000
 And he knows what market. 

00:27:29.120 --> 00:27:36.000
 He thought his order should be the next to be executed ... 

00:27:36.120 --> 00:27:39.720
 but it was not. It is impossible to know. 

00:27:39.840 --> 00:27:44.000
 When someone started to explain to me, it was easy to understand the rest. 

00:27:44.120 --> 00:27:48.880
 But if you don't know there are resellers ... 

00:27:49.000 --> 00:27:53.800
 who will use certain types of orders to double you, buy tickets ... 

00:27:53.920 --> 00:27:56.160
 and resell them to those who queue ... 

00:27:56.280 --> 00:28:02.360
 If you don't know that a considerable number of transactions are taking place ... 

00:28:02.480 --> 00:28:05.320
 if you don't know how it works ... 

00:28:05.440 --> 00:28:09.200
 you believe what you see on the price stream. 

00:28:09.320 --> 00:28:13.680
 Who is organizing this? - He's not a businessman ... 

00:28:13.800 --> 00:28:17.120
 who created these characteristics. 

00:28:17.240 --> 00:28:22.880
 Very few people have the technical skills ... 

00:28:23.000 --> 00:28:25.280
 to create these characteristics. 

