 Dave Lauer was a trader and analyst at Allston and Citadel, THF companies. 

00:29:04.800 --> 00:29:08.600
 He testified as an expert at the Senate committee hearing ... 

00:29:08.720 --> 00:29:11.920
 on high frequency trading. 

00:29:12.040 --> 00:29:15.360
 Like Bodek, he is one of the few initiates ... 

00:29:15.480 --> 00:29:18.880
 who talked about their experiences. 

00:29:20.240 --> 00:29:22.880
 At the top, there is THF ... 

00:29:23.000 --> 00:29:25.480
 and trading for own account in major banks. 

00:29:25.600 --> 00:29:28.280
 These are the main ... 

00:29:28.400 --> 00:29:35.480
 This is the part that everyone is trying to observe or integrate. 

00:29:35.600 --> 00:29:37.360
 Below, there is the Stock Exchange. 

00:29:37.480 --> 00:29:42.600
 And the stock market economic model concerns volume. 

00:29:42.720 --> 00:29:47.600
 The stock exchanges are doing everything to attract THF ... 

00:29:47.720 --> 00:29:51.000
 in their premises, and therefore, to attract volume. 

00:29:51.120 --> 00:29:54.440
 Couriers are those who transmit orders to stock exchanges ... 

00:29:54.560 --> 00:29:59.120
 and they earn money from the commissions of their "buy-siders". 

00:29:59.240 --> 00:30:01.600
 At the bottom of the pyramid, there is the "buy side" ... 

00:30:01.720 --> 00:30:05.120
 which brings together pension funds and investment funds. 

00:30:05.240 --> 00:30:08.280
 These are the investors, those who are there ... 

00:30:08.400 --> 00:30:13.400
 because they think a business has a solid foundation or a future. 

00:30:13.520 --> 00:30:17.280
 The amount of money generated by all of these parties ... 

00:30:17.400 --> 00:30:21.640
 represents the cost ... - Yes, it is the cost of transactions. 

00:30:21.760 --> 00:30:26.280
 When an investment or pension fund executes a large order ... 

00:30:26.400 --> 00:30:29.800
 what is this order in traders' jargon called? 

00:30:30.960 --> 00:30:33.800
 It's donated money ... 

00:30:33.920 --> 00:30:39.920
 it's easy money, it's cake ... 

00:30:42.080 --> 00:30:43.520
 this is what is expected. 

00:30:43.640 --> 00:30:47.360
 These algorithms are used to detect what is happening. 

00:30:47.480 --> 00:30:51.320
 It's about understanding when institutions buy and sell. 

00:30:51.440 --> 00:30:54.640
 They are waiting for my pension money to reach ... 

00:30:54.760 --> 00:30:57.680
 Yes, they will bite you a little. 

00:30:57.800 --> 00:31:01.800
 It is a slow death. We put you aside ... 

00:31:01.920 --> 00:31:06.800
 at the time this order goes through the system. 

00:31:08.520 --> 00:31:13.040
 You have to be on the other side of the transaction to make money. 

00:31:18.320 --> 00:31:23.400
 It's been like this for a long time, people are used to it, they accept it. 

00:31:23.520 --> 00:31:26.240
 They know they are being scammed. 

00:31:26.360 --> 00:31:30.920
 On Wall Street, you are necessarily scammed unless you are the scammer. 

00:31:31.040 --> 00:31:37.200
 Those who put their money in pension and investment funds ... 

00:31:37.320 --> 00:31:41.000
 they don't understand what's going on. 

00:31:41.120 --> 00:31:44.400
 If they understood that the banks ... 

00:31:44.520 --> 00:31:50.640
 take their money and declare it as profit ... 

00:31:50.760 --> 00:31:52.560
 they would do something. 

00:31:52.680 --> 00:31:57.720
 But the problem is, it's too complicated for people to understand. 

00:31:57.840 --> 00:32:03.880
 I thought it was funny when the problem of order types broke out. 

00:32:04.000 --> 00:32:10.160
 It is obvious that many people did not know ... 

00:32:10.280 --> 00:32:13.320
 that these markets offered special order types. 

00:32:13.440 --> 00:32:19.440
 90% of financiers do not know how the American stock market works. 

00:32:34.440 --> 00:32:38.720
 Before, it was the brokers who owned the stock exchanges. 

00:32:38.840 --> 00:32:42.320
 They were integrating new businesses into the financial market ... 

00:32:42.440 --> 00:32:49.160
 hoping to sell the stocks of these companies to their clients ... 

00:32:49.280 --> 00:32:51.880
 and obtain fees for this sale. 

00:32:52.000 --> 00:32:56.560
 These businesses would grow, be successful, and everything would be fine. 

00:32:56.680 --> 00:32:59.680
 On the other hand, what is different in all of this ... 

00:32:59.800 --> 00:33:04.760
 is that these scholarships were acquired in majority ... 

00:33:04.880 --> 00:33:07.680
 by companies with private capital. 

00:33:07.800 --> 00:33:10.280
 They are not necessarily intended ... 

00:33:10.400 --> 00:33:14.720
 develop small businesses and get them listed on the stock market ... 

00:33:14.840 --> 00:33:18.760
 but rather to generate monthly income. 

00:33:18.880 --> 00:33:24.440
 High frequency trading ensures a gain for each transaction. 

00:33:24.560 --> 00:33:28.560
 So if we manage to make transactions frequently ... 

00:33:28.680 --> 00:33:33.560
 the profits generated make it possible to create a profit. 

00:33:33.680 --> 00:33:37.320
 These THF companies benefit from the complexity ... 

00:33:37.440 --> 00:33:43.120
 as they understand it, their function is to study the market structure. 

00:33:43.240 --> 00:33:47.160
 They understand and exploit market inefficiencies. 

00:33:48.760 --> 00:33:51.360
 The scholarships are over ... 

00:33:51.480 --> 00:33:54.440
 places where companies attracted investors ... 

00:33:54.560 --> 00:33:58.280
 to data centers where wars are waged by algorithms ... 

00:33:58.400 --> 00:34:02.040
 who transact at the speed of light. 

00:34:02.160 --> 00:34:06.000
 An invisible world which, during a sudden collapse ... 

00:34:06.120 --> 00:34:09.200
 the infamous 2010 lightning crash ... 

00:34:09.320 --> 00:34:13.640
 saw $ 862 billion evaporate ... 

00:34:13.760 --> 00:34:17.400
 in a few minutes on the American financial market. 

00:34:19.120 --> 00:34:21.720
 Wow! Almost 1000 points! 

00:34:21.840 --> 00:34:24.280
 We call it a capitulation. 

00:34:24.400 --> 00:34:29.320
 They will suspend the transactions, we cannot stop the sale. 

00:34:29.440 --> 00:34:34.080
 For me, the lightning crash was a defining moment. 

00:34:34.200 --> 00:34:36.320
 I couldn't ignore it. 

00:34:36.440 --> 00:34:38.800
 I was on the THF floor. 

00:34:38.920 --> 00:34:43.480
 Everything was fine, finally, the markets were down 2.5%. 

00:34:43.600 --> 00:34:45.760
 We saw the riots in Greece on television. 

00:34:45.880 --> 00:34:50.840
 Each time they rioted, the markets went down. 

00:34:52.520 --> 00:34:56.360
 I remember watching, each floor broadcast CNBC. 

00:34:56.480 --> 00:35:00.720
 I saw that the Dow Jones index lost 100 points ... 

00:35:00.840 --> 00:35:04.840
 I said to myself: "Too bad", and I continued to work. 

00:35:04.960 --> 00:35:08.600
 A minute later, I see that he lost another 100 points. 

00:35:08.720 --> 00:35:12.840
 I get up and go to the futures traders office. 

00:35:12.960 --> 00:35:16.400
 They are very restless, they don't know what's going on. 

00:35:16.520 --> 00:35:20.800
 They had a lot of orders on the market, it's chaos. 

00:35:20.920 --> 00:35:23.160
 100 more points are lost. 

00:35:23.280 --> 00:35:27.080
 The CEO of the company comes running and shouts: 

00:35:27.200 --> 00:35:28.840
 "Stop it all!" 

00:35:28.960 --> 00:35:32.640
 They press the buttons, they turn everything off. 

00:35:32.760 --> 00:35:37.440
 We are all grouped around these two screens. 

00:35:37.560 --> 00:35:40.280
 On a screen, we look at the accounts ... 

00:35:40.400 --> 00:35:45.880
 this is the futures market, people are ready to buy ... 

00:35:46.000 --> 00:35:48.520
 and others for sale is the market. 

00:35:48.640 --> 00:35:53.840
 As we look at the screen, the orders begin to decrease ... 

00:35:53.960 --> 00:36:00.000
 orders are canceled, they decrease further, they disappear from the screen ... 

00:36:00.120 --> 00:36:03.640
 and then there is nothing left. There was no more market. 

00:36:03.760 --> 00:36:07.560
 For a few seconds, there was no more market. 

00:36:07.680 --> 00:36:11.000
 We are all seated, we observe the emptiness. 

00:36:11.120 --> 00:36:13.640
 We have no idea what's going to happen. 

00:36:13.760 --> 00:36:16.880
 I thought something horrible had just happened ... 

00:36:17.000 --> 00:36:21.520
 something indescribable, the market was gone. 

00:36:21.640 --> 00:36:24.840
 I called my bargaining office and said: 

00:36:24.960 --> 00:36:28.920
 "What is happening ?" They replied, "We don't know." 

00:36:29.040 --> 00:36:33.080
 I said, "What are you doing? Are you expanding your markets?" 

00:36:33.200 --> 00:36:37.800
 They said that is what they were doing. I thought there was only that to do. 

00:36:37.920 --> 00:36:41.000
 Let's wait until it stops. 

00:36:41.120 --> 00:36:44.680
 We were almost nauseated, we were worried ... 

00:36:44.800 --> 00:36:48.840
 we didn't know if the world was going to stop. 

00:36:48.960 --> 00:36:52.840
 Even the September 11 attacks did not have this impact. 

00:36:52.960 --> 00:36:58.040
 Things returned to normal, the market started again ... 

00:36:58.160 --> 00:37:01.760
 it went up suddenly, activities resumed. 

00:37:01.880 --> 00:37:06.120
 Personally, I changed after that. 

00:37:06.240 --> 00:37:09.600
 That day, I stopped believing in capitalism ... 

00:37:09.720 --> 00:37:13.720
 finally, to the capitalism that we had built. 

00:37:13.840 --> 00:37:17.440
 I had lost confidence in this system. 

00:37:19.440 --> 00:37:23.800
 My friend has a doctorate in climate science, he worked at Harvard. 

00:37:23.920 --> 00:37:27.480
 Next to me, there was a doctoral student in bioinformatics ... 

00:37:27.600 --> 00:37:30.320
 on the other side, a semiconductor designer ... 

00:37:30.440 --> 00:37:34.080
 behind me, someone who had a master's degree in math from MIT. 

00:37:34.200 --> 00:37:38.200
 These people mobilize their impressive gray matter ... 

00:37:38.320 --> 00:37:42.880
 and use it to make money in a THF system. 

00:37:43.000 --> 00:37:48.040
 I couldn't justify it anymore. 

00:37:48.160 --> 00:37:51.800
 They should have worked in research ... 

00:37:51.920 --> 00:37:54.280
 against cancer or climate change. 

00:37:54.400 --> 00:37:57.440
 And there they were, earning a fortune. 

00:37:57.560 --> 00:38:02.640
 Were the markets, their efficiency, their stability improved? 

00:38:02.760 --> 00:38:04.680
 That day, we knew we weren't. 

00:38:50.400 --> 00:38:51.680
 It's bad. 

00:38:51.800 --> 00:38:55.240
 There you know you have to stop. 

00:38:55.360 --> 00:39:03.640
 We spent the whole day doing this. This algorithm brought in 200 dollars. 

00:39:03.760 --> 00:39:06.160
 It has gone back to 471 now. 

